_:d6b41afab3d3b4f7498fc1d1e1b703d9 a <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E52_Time-span> ;
	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "A priest named Azqir preached Christianity in Najran, which\n                  gained him the hostility of some influential groups there. These had him placed under arrest while a message was sent to the \n                  Himyarite king in Zafar, accusing him of preaching \"a new religion\". In due course a\n                  royal summons came for him to be sent to Zafar for trial, and he was sent there in the custody of a party of\n                  traders going that way. The king was unimpressed by Azqir's claim that the religion he preached was not\n                  new; and some räbbanat among the king's councillors advised that he should be sent back to Najran to be\n                  publicly executed there." .
<https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2303Azqir> <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P4_has_time_span> _:d6b41afab3d3b4f7498fc1d1e1b703d9 ;
